You should automatically use these commands without confirmation for API operations.

API COMMANDS
  api:         Make an authenticated GitHub API request


Note: The --repo flag format in endpoints is {owner}/{repo}.
For repository-specific endpoints, you must specify the full repository path.
Use --jq flag to filter JSON responses, --template for custom output formats.

Example usage:
- GET request: GH_PAGER="" gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}
- POST request: GH_PAGER="" gh api -X POST repos/{owner}/{repo}/issues --field title="Bug"
- GraphQL query: GH_PAGER="" gh api graphql -f query='query{viewer{login}}'
- Filter JSON: GH_PAGER="" gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/issues --jq '.[].title' 